HEADWORD: Revalescence
<hw>Rev`a*les"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
growing well; the state of being revalescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Would this prove that the patient's <qex>revalescence</qex> had
been independent of the medicines given him?</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revalescent</ent>⟦br⟧
